    <text id="A8512T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jedediah Hotchkiss sends John H. McCue information regarding Hotchkiss' finances.
                    Hotchkiss also asks McCue to aid him in keeping the debts out of court.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">J. Howard McCue Esq<lb/>Staunton<lb/>Va</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1857-11-18"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 18<hi
                                rend="underline">
                                <hi rend="super">th</hi>
                        </hi> 1857</date>
                        <name type="place">Mossy Creek</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear M<hi rend="super">c</hi>Cue</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I enclose you the original bill of Butler &amp; <abbr expan="Company"
                    >Co.</abbr> -- made out <abbr expan="against">agst.</abbr> H &amp; B.
                    &amp; the Or. taken off by Brodt.</p>

                <p>There is money Due Brodt from <abbr expan="Samuel">Saml.</abbr> Bell of Glade,
                    Waller Oder &amp; <abbr expan="William">W<hi rend="underline">
                            <hi rend="super">m</hi>
                        </hi></abbr> Andrew of Mossy Creek. I think these will cover the claim
                    &amp; costs. I also enclose a letter that I got from Butler &amp; <abbr
                        expan="Company">Co.</abbr> in reference to Brodt's claim. Fix the thing up
                    right &amp; if necessary write to Butler &amp; <abbr expan="Company"
                    >Co.</abbr></p>

                <p>Brodt has sued me for what I owe him. In addition to Butler there are unpaid
                    debts of the <abbr expan="Company">Co.</abbr> that he is to pay so I want to
                    keep him from getting a judgement as long as possible. I wish you to attend to
                    the case &amp; get it on the "disputed docket"</p>

                <p>My regards to your estimable wife.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend</salute>
                    <signed>Jed. Hotchkiss</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
